events.description: Battle of Mogyoród: Dukes Géza and Ladislaus defeat their cousin Solomon, King of Hungary, forcing him to flee to Hungary's western borderland.

events.html: • 1590 – Battle of Ivry: Henry of Navarre and the Huguenots defeat the forces of the Catholic League under Charles, Duke of Mayenne, during the French Wars of Religion.[2]

events.html: • 1647 – Thirty Years' War: Bavaria, Cologne, France and Sweden sign the Truce of Ulm.[3]

events.description: According to his own account, Otto von Guericke completes his book Experimenta Nova (ut vocantur) Magdeburgica de Vacuo Spatio, detailing his experiments on vacuum and his discovery of electrostatic repulsion.
events.html: • 1663 – According to his own account, Otto von Guericke completes his book Experimenta Nova (ut vocantur) Magdeburgica de Vacuo Spatio, detailing his experiments on vacuum and his discovery of electrostatic repulsion.[4]

events.description: The Third Anglo-Dutch War: The Battle of Ronas Voe results in the Dutch East India Company ship Wapen van Rotterdam being captured with a death toll of up to 300 Dutch crew and soldiers.
events.html: • 1674 – The Third Anglo-Dutch War: The Battle of Ronas Voe results in the Dutch East India Company ship Wapen van Rotterdam being captured with a death toll of up to 300 Dutch crew and soldiers.[5]

events.description: Admiral Sir John Byng is executed by firing squad aboard HMS Monarch for breach of the Articles of War.
events.html: • 1757 – Admiral Sir John Byng is executed by firing squad aboard HMS Monarch for breach of the Articles of War.[6]

events.description: American Revolutionary War: Spanish forces capture Fort Charlotte in Mobile, Alabama, the last British frontier post capable of threatening New Orleans.
events.html: • 1780 – American Revolutionary War: Spanish forces capture Fort Charlotte in Mobile, Alabama, the last British frontier post capable of threatening New Orleans.[7]

events.description: Eli Whitney is granted a patent for the cotton gin.
events.html: • 1794 – Eli Whitney is granted a patent for the cotton gin.[8]

events.description: Rossini's Petite messe solennelle is first performed, by twelve singers, two pianists and a harmonium player in a mansion in Paris.
events.html: • 1864 – Rossini's Petite messe solennelle is first performed, by twelve singers, two pianists and a harmonium player in a mansion in Paris.[9]

events.description: The Mikado, a light opera by W. S. Gilbert and Arthur Sullivan, receives its first public performance at the Savoy Theatre in London.
events.html: • 1885 – The Mikado, a light opera by W. S. Gilbert and Arthur Sullivan, receives its first public performance at the Savoy Theatre in London.[10]

events.description: The Gold Standard Act is ratified, placing the United States currency on the gold standard.
events.html: • 1900 – The Gold Standard Act is ratified, placing the United States currency on the gold standard.[11]

events.description: Utah governor Heber Manning Wells vetoes a bill that would have eased restriction on polygamy.
events.html: • 1901 – Utah governor Heber Manning Wells vetoes a bill that would have eased restriction on polygamy.[12]

events.description: Pelican Island National Wildlife Refuge, the first national wildlife refuge in the US, is established by President Theodore Roosevelt.
events.html: • 1903 – Pelican Island National Wildlife Refuge, the first national wildlife refuge in the US, is established by President Theodore Roosevelt.[13]

events.description: In the second of the 1920 Schleswig plebiscites, about 80% of the population in Zone II votes to remain part of Weimar Germany.
events.html: • 1920 – In the second of the 1920 Schleswig plebiscites, about 80% of the population in Zone II votes to remain part of Weimar Germany.[14]

events.description: Six members of a group of Irish Republican Army activists known as the Forgotten Ten, are hanged in Dublin's Mountjoy Prison.
events.html: • 1921 – Six members of a group of Irish Republican Army activists known as the Forgotten Ten, are hanged in Dublin's Mountjoy Prison.[15]

events.description: Charlie Daly and three other members of the Irish Republican Army are executed by Irish Free State forces.
events.html: • 1923 – Charlie Daly and three other members of the Irish Republican Army are executed by Irish Free State forces.[16]

events.description: The El Virilla train accident, Costa Rica, kills 248 people and wounds another 93 when a train falls off a bridge over the Río Virilla between Heredia and Tibás.
events.html: • 1926 – The El Virilla train accident, Costa Rica, kills 248 people and wounds another 93 when a train falls off a bridge over the Río Virilla between Heredia and Tibás.[17]

events.description: Alam Ara, India's first talking film, is released.
events.html: • 1931 – Alam Ara, India's first talking film, is released.[18]

events.description: Slovakia declares independence under German pressure.
events.html: • 1939 – Slovakia declares independence under German pressure.[19]

events.description: Anne Miller becomes the first American patient to be treated with penicillin, under the care of Orvan Hess and John Bumstead.
events.html: • 1942 – Anne Miller becomes the first American patient to be treated with penicillin, under the care of Orvan Hess and John Bumstead.[20]

events.description: The Holocaust: The liquidation of the Kraków Ghetto is completed.
events.html: • 1943 – The Holocaust: The liquidation of the Kraków Ghetto is completed.[21]

events.description: The R.A.F. drop the Grand Slam bomb in action for the first time, on a railway viaduct near Bielefeld, Germany.
events.html: • 1945 – The R.A.F. drop the Grand Slam bomb in action for the first time, on a railway viaduct near Bielefeld, Germany.[22]

events.description: Korean War: United Nations troops recapture Seoul for the second time.
events.html: • 1951 – Korean War: United Nations troops recapture Seoul for the second time.[23]

events.description: A USAF B-52 bomber crashes near Yuba City, California whilst carrying nuclear weapons.
events.html: • 1961 – A USAF B-52 bomber crashes near Yuba City, California whilst carrying nuclear weapons.[24]

events.description: Jack Ruby is convicted of killing Lee Harvey Oswald, the assumed assassin of John F. Kennedy.

events.html: • 1967 – The body of U.S. President John F. Kennedy is moved to a permanent burial place at Arlington National Cemetery.[26]

events.description: The Israel Defense Forces launch Operation Litani, a seven-day campaign to invade and occupy southern Lebanon.

events.description: Alia Royal Jordanian Flight 600 crashes at Doha International Airport, killing 45 people.
events.html: • 1979 – Alia Royal Jordanian Flight 600 crashes at Doha International Airport, killing 45 people.[29]
